news.title: RLDA invites bid for residential development in Prayagraj
news.para: This proposed site for residential development is rectangular in shape and is well connected to an extensive network of rail, road, and air. It is about 25 kilometer away from the Prayagraj airport, while the Jhusi railway station is situated just in front of the proposed site.

news.title: Institutional investments in real estate down 17% in 2021 at $4 billion: Report
news.para: As per the data, the institutional investments in office assets fell to USD 1,248 million last year from USD 2,199 million in 2020 calendar year. Similarly, the inflows in mixed-use development projects dipped to USD 182 million from USD 1,616 million.

news.title: Ajmera Realty to invest Rs 110 crore to redevelop housing society in Mumbai
news.para: "The company will invest approximately Rs 110 crore to redevelop the housing project as part of its plan to expand footprint and build residential properties in key prime markets of Mumbai," Ajmera Realty said in a statement.

news.title: Corbett director issued show-cause notice over illegal constructions
news.para: The move came a day after former chief wildlife warden of the state, JS Suhag, had been issued a show-cause notice by additional chief secretary Anand Bardhan for failing to use his authority to stop the illegalities.

news.title: Poor urban design eats into 28% of urban land in Ahmedabad: Study
news.para: Overall in Ahmedabad, a study carried out by CEPT University students under City Studio project found that there are 28% such unutilized open spaces.

news.title: Architects want say in urban planning, write to Punjab CM
news.para: Goel, who is also chairman of the Punjab Architects Association, has suggested to the CM that projects be made for the entire city instead of select areas.

news.title: Seventeen families from TNUHDB tenements collapsed at Tiruvottiyur allotted alternate units
news.para: While the remaining 11 families have sought houses in the same premises at Tiruvottiyur after reconstruction, the release said, financial assistance of Rs. 24,000 would be given to the respective families for staying elsewhere during the reconstruction period.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh to give Rs 1,000 maintenance allowance to 1.5 crore workers
news.para: There are 5,09,08,745 registered workers in the state out of whom, the number of unorganized workers registered on the e-SHRAM portal are 3,81,60,725. The total number of workers registered under BOCW Board are 1,27,48,020.

news.title: China Evergrande Group shares halted, set to release 'inside information'
news.para: Evergrande, the world's most indebted developer, is struggling to repay more than $300 billion in liabilities, including nearly $20 billion of international market bonds that were deemed to be in cross-default by ratings firms last month after it missed payments.

news.title: Telangana industries minister urges centre to reopen CCI unit at Adilabad
news.para: Rama Rao wrote letters in this regard to Union Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman and Union Minister for Heavy Industries Mahendra Nath Pandey, a release from his office said.

news.title: Mumbai: Brothers con dozens on pretext of villa bookings, arrested
news.para: They had duped at least 12 people in 2021 with fake information after obtaining photos of the bungalows and villas with amenities from hotel booking websites and posted them on their Instagram page (luxury.villas.lonavala), police said.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh plans energy efficient appliances for houses in Jagananna colonies
news.para: ​These appliances are expected to save 3,598 on electricity bills of each house. On the whole, the annual energy savings of 15 lakh houses are estimated at 1,674 million units worth 539.7 crore.

news.title: Premium FSI discount rakes in Rs 1,527 crore in nine months for Pune civic body
news.para: As against an annual target of Rs1,185 crore, the PMC has so far earned Rs1,527 crore from building permissions. A discount in premium FSI and relaxation from lockdown restrictions have boosted the department's revenue.

news.title: Rajasthan government to take Rs 200 crore loan from centre to build houses for poor
news.para: ​The urban housing department had earlier proposed to construct nearly 23,000 houses for economic weaker section (EWS) and lower income group (LIG) across the state under public-private and partnership (PPP) model.

news.title: Bengaluru Metro will have 170km network, 17 lakh ridership by 2024: BMRCL MD
news.para: Parwez said: “Challaghatta station (2km Kengeri-Challaghatta extension) will be ready by September 2022 and the 3km stretch of Nagasandra-Bangalore International Exhibition Centre (Madavara) will be operational by October-November 2022”.
